        <definition>VLC_API void vlc_fifo_Unlock</definition>
        <argsstring>(vlc_fifo_t *)</argsstring>
        <name>vlc_fifo_Unlock</name>
        <param>
          <type>vlc_fifo_t *</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Unlocks a block FIFO.</para>
<para>The calling thread must have locked the FIFO previously with <ref refid="group__fifo_1gae03d77fb47001cfb35223b0b3cdc28df" kindref="member">vlc_fifo_Lock()</ref>. Otherwise, the behaviour is undefined.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>This function is not a cancellation point. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
