      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__fifo_1ga3907f356b23df01c92864fd7eba77295" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>VLC_API void</type>
        <definition>VLC_API void vlc_fifo_Wait</definition>
        <argsstring>(vlc_fifo_t *)</argsstring>
        <name>vlc_fifo_Wait</name>
        <param>
          <type>vlc_fifo_t *</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Waits on the FIFO.</para>
<para>Atomically unlocks the FIFO and waits until one thread signals the FIFO, then locks the FIFO again. A signal can be sent by queueing a block to the previously empty FIFO or by calling <ref refid="group__fifo_1gad4157ac4c846ae51abfc96837b4c2ac3" kindref="member">vlc_fifo_Signal()</ref> directly. This function may also return spuriously at any moment.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>This function is a cancellation point. In case of cancellation, the the FIFO will be locked before cancellation cleanup handlers are processed. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
